-- Bain, Lion Capital Close to Bid for Afflelou, Le Figaro Says
-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 2012-04-28T09:44:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/bain-lion-capital-close-to-bid-for-afflelou-le-figaro-says.html
Private-equity firms Bain Capital
LLC and  Lion Capital LLP  may bid in the coming days to buy a
majority stake in French eyeglass maker Alain Afflelou SA,  Le
Figaro  reported, without identifying its sources.  The winning bidder would need to raise about 300 million
euros ($398 million) through debt to buy out stakes held by
Bridgepoint and  Apax Partners , Le Figaro said. Bridgepoint owns
57 percent and Apax 20 percent in Afflelou, the newspaper said.
Founder Alain Afflelou may increase his stake, currently at 22
percent, Le Figaro said.  Afflelou is valued at about 800 million euros, Le Figaro
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
